             <h2 class="text-2xl md:text-3xl font-bold font-playfair text-slate-900 mb-8 border-l-4 border-indigo-600 pl-4">Linear Algebra</h2>
             <p class="text-lg text-slate-600 font-light leading-relaxed">
                 Based on <strong>Artin's Algebra</strong>, this course covers core concepts of linear algebra. It starts with Subspaces of $\textbf{R}^{n}$ and introduces the concept of Fields. The definition and properties of Vector Spaces are discussed, followed by Bases and Dimension, techniques for Computing with Bases, and Direct Sums. The course then moves to Linear Operators, the Dimension Formula, and representing linear maps using the Matrix of a Linear Transformation. Key topics like Eigenvectors and Eigenvalues, the Characteristic Polynomial, and finding Triangular and Diagonal Forms are also covered.
             </p>
